        "data": {
          "title": "Logged Out",
          "content": "You wake up to the sound of a dial-up modem screaming in the dark.\n\nAt first, you think it is a memory. Then you realize the sound is coming from inside your chest.\n\nYou are lying on a carpeted floor in a room lit by the blue glow of an old CRT monitor. The air smells like dust, ozone, and rain through an open window. On the screen, a blinking cursor waits beneath a single sentence:\n\nUSER SESSION ENDED.\n\nYou remember pain. Headlights. A wet road. The weightless moment before impact.\n\nThen nothing.\n\nNow this.\n\nThe monitor flickers.\n\nWelcome to the Dead Web.",
